<h1>Typography</h1>
<p>
  As a timeless, highly effective font, Helvetica is at the forefront of the Fandom brand and used across our mobile
  and desktop site and is available in various weights. Our native apps inherit the respective default fonts —
  San Francisco on iOS and Roboto on Android — and also contain various weights.
</p>
<p>
  Note: the 10px size should be displayed in all caps only to ensure proper readability.
</p>
<p>
  It"s recommended to use available typography variables to keep consistency across products.
</p>

<section>
  <h2 id="font-family">Font Family</h2>
  <p>
    For highest browser compatibility we decided to follow direction described
    in
    <a
      href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/11/using-system-ui-fonts-practical-guide/"
    >
      Using System UI Fonts In Web Design: A Quick Practical Guide
    </a>. It provides a
    list of font-families for browsers to fallback. We listed font-families
    supported by major operating systems and finally we fall back to <code>sans-serif</code>.
    This way we can avoid web-font delivery process which would hit page
    performance.
  </p>
  <code><span class="format-code">$wds-font-family</span>: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;</code>

</section>

<section>
  <h2 id="news-stories-font">News and stories and Mobile Article font family</h2>
  <p> News and Stories and uses Rubik as it"s primary font.</p>
  <code><span class="format-code">$wds-fandom-font-family</span>: Rubik, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;</code>
</section>

